# Git: commit + push after tasks; deploy on command only

## Commit and push (default after tasks)

When you **finish a task** (code/config fixes, mobile or web changes, scripts, Cursor rules, etc.) and the working tree has **uncommitted changes** from that work, **`git commit`** and **`git push`** to **`origin`** on the **current branch** before ending the turn.

**Skip commit/push** only if: the working tree is **clean**, or the user **explicitly** asked you not to commit in that message.

Use a concise, accurate commit message. Never commit secrets or gitignored env files.

## Coolify deploy (user command only)

Do **not** run **`npm run deploy:coolify`** or any deploy webhook unless the user **explicitly** asks to **deploy** in the current message.

If they ask to **deploy** and the tree is dirty, **commit and push first**, then run **`npm run deploy:coolify`** only after their deploy request (same message or follow-up).
